    </para>
    <para id="S4.p2">
      <p>Ahlfors' Lemma gives the principal criterion for obtaining lower bounds
on the Kobayashi metric.
<theorem id="Thmx2"><caption position="right" separator=".">Ahlfors' Lemma</caption><para id="Thmx2.p1"><p><text font="italic">Let <Math mode="inline" tex="ds^{2}=h(z)|dz|^{2}" text="d * s ^ 2 = h * z * | * d * z * | ^ 2"><XMath><XMApp><XMTok meaning="eq" role="RELOP" font="upright">=</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">d</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">s</XMTok><XMTok meaning="2" role="NUMBER" font="upright">2</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp><XMApp><XMTok role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" possibleFunction="yes">h</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" open="(" close=")">z</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" font="upright">|</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">d</XMTok><XMTok role="UNKNOWN">z</XMTok><XMApp><XMTok role="SUPERSCRIPTOP"/><XMTok role="UNKNOWN" font="upright">|</XMTok><XMTok meaning="2" role="NUMBER" font="upright">2</XMTok></XMApp></XMApp></XMApp></XMath></Math> be a Hermitian pseudo-metric on
